  "texts": [
    "For data processing, we convert the event data into 10 ms \"frames\" using a causal eventvolume binning strategy to minimize latency for online inference (Fig. 3.C).",
    "Data augmentation during training includes spatio-temporal affine augmentations directly on the events (including temporal + polarity flips, but excluding spatial reflections).Implementation Details.",
    "For training, we use a batch size of 32, where each batch consists of 50 event frames.",
    "We train for 200 epochs with the AdamW optimizer with a base learning rate of 0.002 and a weight decay of 0.005.",
    "We use the cosine decay with linear warmup scheduler, with warmup steps equal to 0.025 of the total training steps."
  ],
